result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy J Fisher was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take >$500 - $5000), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Timothy J Fisher in court, in custody, with attorney Amber K. Rumpf.   Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  State moves to strikes the repeater provision.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1. Court finds defendant guilty.  Court conducts plea colloquy with defendant.  State makes sentencing recommendation.  Defense makes sentencing recommendation.  

The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

3 1/2 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 197 days).  Concurrent to current sentence.  
  -  1 1/2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*No contact with:  WalMart.

RESTITUTION:  $175.00 to WalMart (to be converted to a civil judgment);

COURT COSTS:  $278.00 (to be converted to a civil judgment);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be converted to a civil judgment);
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
